-- Sparks, Swenson, Tourre Discuss Goldman's Role in Crisis: Video
-- 
-- 2010-04-27T19:00:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-27/sparks-tourre-discuss-goldman-s-role-in-crisis.html

          
          
             Daniel Sparks, former head of 
Goldman Sachs Group Inc.'s mortgage business, Michael Swenson, a
managing director for the structured products group at Goldman, 
and Fabrice Tourre, executive director of structured products 
group trading, comment on Goldman's role during the financial 
crisis and their conduct at the time.  
 The spoke at the Senate Permanent Subcommittee on 
Investigations hearing on Goldman. (This is an excerpt from the 
Senate hearing. Source: Bloomberg)  
